Stenoma aplytopis is a moth in the family Depressariidae. It was described by Edward Meyrick in 1930. It is found in Par√°, Brazil.The wingspan is about 13 mm. The forewings are whitish, irregularly sprinkled grey. The plical and second discal stigmata are blackish with a marginal series of blackish dots or marks around the posterior third of the costa and termen. The hindwings are grey whitish.